text: Kim Yeon-ji (born 12 May 1981) is a South Korean taekwondo practitioner. She won a gold medal in lightweight at the 2001 World Taekwondo Championships, and another gold medal in lightweight at the 2003 World Taekwondo Championships in Garmisch-Partenkirchen. She won a gold medal at the 2002 Asian Games. ==References== ==External links== * Category:1981 births Category:Living people Category:South Korean female taekwondo practitioners Category:Taekwondo practitioners at the 2002 Asian Games Category:Asian Games medalists in taekwondo Category:Medalists at the 2002 Asian Games Category:Asian Games gold medalists for South Korea Category:World Taekwondo Championships medalists
